cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with finite automata and their ambiguity.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents efficient algorithms for testing ambiguity.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper mentions an application of the algorithms to computing the entropy of a probabilistic automaton.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possibility as ambiguity in automata is relevant to certain areas of machine learning.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possibility as the paper discusses the complexities of the algorithms presented.
